WEBVTT

00:01.600 --> 00:02.700
No, no, no.

00:02.766 --> 00:04.733
Don't touch that dial.

00:04.800 --> 00:07.900
Here's what's
on my mind, tonight.

00:10.166 --> 00:13.466
A veteran photographer was

00:10.166 --> 00:13.466
one last shot at the big time.

00:13.533 --> 00:15.000
Halloween issue, key layout.

00:15.066 --> 00:17.266
- 'You still have the touch?'
- Razor sharp.

00:17.333 --> 00:20.400
But high fashion
demands a cutting edge.

00:20.466 --> 00:22.600
- You want to make her scream?
- Yes.

00:22.666 --> 00:24.800
So, an expert
gets into the picture.

00:24.866 --> 00:26.333
Hey, babe!

00:26.400 --> 00:29.433
But who will pay the high
cost for Freddy's services?

00:29.500 --> 00:31.633
Keep the motivation,
Kiki, it's wonderful.

00:31.700 --> 00:34.733
A special Halloween treat
on "Freddy's Nightmares".

00:55.233 --> 00:57.600
You're in Springwood, now.

00:57.666 --> 00:59.733
And you're all mine!

02:13.600 --> 02:15.633
Do we have to say cheese?

02:15.700 --> 02:17.100
Cheese?

02:17.166 --> 02:19.433
Yeah, you always
have us say cheese.

02:19.500 --> 02:21.000
'Our cue to smile.'

02:21.066 --> 02:23.300
Yeah, I like to say cheese

02:23.366 --> 02:25.466
Yes, you can say cheese.

02:25.533 --> 02:26.833
Always works like a charm.

02:26.900 --> 02:29.833
Every year your pictures

02:26.900 --> 02:29.833
come to us and they look great!

02:29.900 --> 02:32.366
- So..
- Must be the cheese.

02:32.433 --> 02:34.866
Well, it seems to
capture the moment just great.

02:34.933 --> 02:38.800
'Alright, now you hold that.'

02:38.866 --> 02:39.800
Okay, good.

02:39.866 --> 02:43.100
And cheese!

02:43.166 --> 02:45.233
Cheese!

02:45.300 --> 02:46.766
All set!

02:46.833 --> 02:49.133
Okay, I will have
these for you real soon.

02:49.200 --> 02:50.700
Thank you, very much.

02:50.766 --> 02:53.000
Do you realize, you've taken
our annual family portrait

02:53.066 --> 02:54.666
since Debbie was three.

02:54.733 --> 02:56.700
Oh, I didn't realize
it had been so long.

02:56.766 --> 02:58.266
We hope you've enjoyed
watching her grow up

02:58.333 --> 03:01.233
as much as we have.

03:01.300 --> 03:03.933
Wow, did you
used to be somebody?

03:04.000 --> 03:05.966
Uh, yes!

03:06.033 --> 03:07.000
Thank you.

03:07.066 --> 03:08.866
Oh, this award was when?

03:08.933 --> 03:12.366
Oh, uh, fifteen years ago.

03:12.433 --> 03:15.233
Well, we're honored to have
someone of your caliber

03:15.300 --> 03:16.700
taking our photograph.

03:16.766 --> 03:19.233
And we look forward
to coming back every year

03:19.300 --> 03:20.900
until we're all old and gray.

03:22.366 --> 03:25.500
- Cant wait.
- 'What?'

03:25.566 --> 03:28.900
I said that, uh,
that'd be great.

03:42.466 --> 03:45.633
- Hello.
- 'Hello, is this Stoney Adler?'

03:45.700 --> 03:46.633
You got her.

03:46.700 --> 03:47.933
Is this the right
Stoney Adler?

03:48.000 --> 03:49.900
The one who took the photo
of topless

03:49.966 --> 03:51.900
revisited in silk?

03:51.966 --> 03:55.233
- Yeah, that's my photo.
- 'Great, ever here of Kink?'

03:56.233 --> 03:57.866
Well, I was open to it.

03:57.933 --> 03:59.466
No, the magazine.

03:59.533 --> 04:01.766
Uh, never mind. We're new.
We haven't come out yet.

04:01.833 --> 04:03.300
I'm the editor, Torrie Bodnar.

04:03.366 --> 04:05.166
Oh, good for you.

04:05.233 --> 04:07.166
'We're not men's rag
with sleazy pictures.'

04:07.233 --> 04:09.900
We're culture statement, you
know the art about the bizarre.

04:09.966 --> 04:11.600
We're arresting
and trend setting.

04:11.666 --> 04:13.300
Oh, what do you want with me?

04:13.366 --> 04:14.766
'I haven't seen
your work in years.'

04:14.833 --> 04:17.200
'What happened to you?'

04:17.266 --> 04:20.066
Oh, I was away.

04:20.133 --> 04:21.866
Long trip. How'd you
end up in Springwood?

04:21.933 --> 04:23.900
Is that anywhere
or just nowhere?

04:23.966 --> 04:25.833
It's, uh, somewhere in between.

04:25.900 --> 04:28.766
Umm, what do you want?

04:28.833 --> 04:30.666
When I was a kid,
I loved your work.

04:30.733 --> 04:32.466
Yeah, you sound like
you're still a kid.

04:32.533 --> 04:36.233
'No way. I'm 27 and I need
someone like you on the Kink.'

04:36.300 --> 04:40.100
You're forte was cutting edge,
borderline, wild, racky..

04:40.166 --> 04:41.633
- Racky?
- 'Yeah.'

04:41.700 --> 04:43.633
'Out there, really reaching.'

04:43.700 --> 04:46.466
Oh, right. Racky.

04:46.533 --> 04:49.433
I've got a deadline
if you can handle it.

04:49.500 --> 04:50.533
Try me.

04:50.600 --> 04:52.033
Halloween issue, key layout.

04:52.100 --> 04:54.166
Need it in a week
using top three models.

04:54.233 --> 04:56.766
Do you still have the touch?

04:56.833 --> 04:58.066
Razor sharp.

04:58.133 --> 05:00.833
Great. If this works,
I'd say you're back.

05:07.900 --> 05:11.533
'Now, that's razor sharp.'

05:15.400 --> 05:18.200
Real cuttin' edge.

05:18.266 --> 05:20.066
It's Halloween.

05:20.133 --> 05:21.400
And I'm going to treat

05:21.466 --> 05:25.266
that nice female photographer

05:25.333 --> 05:27.900
to a couple of tricks.

05:32.700 --> 05:36.033
'I love playing head games!'

05:57.866 --> 06:00.566
Oh, I feel stupid.

06:00.633 --> 06:02.766
Try, uh, moving the broom.

06:02.833 --> 06:04.000
It's got splinters.

06:04.066 --> 06:05.900
And the straw itches.

06:05.966 --> 06:09.133
And this-this dress,
it's crawling up my butt.

06:09.200 --> 06:12.066
Alright, alright,
let's break for five.

06:16.166 --> 06:17.300
You know, I only took this

06:17.366 --> 06:19.200
because Kink
is supposed to be so hot.

06:19.266 --> 06:21.200
Only the best.

06:23.033 --> 06:25.033
How come I don't know you?

06:26.966 --> 06:29.133
Does it come as a shock
to you that Paul McCartney

06:29.200 --> 06:31.033
was in another
band before Wings?

06:31.100 --> 06:33.700
Uh, I gotta call my agent, okay?

06:33.766 --> 06:35.533
Yeah. Okay.

06:35.600 --> 06:37.633
Then change for The Ripper.

06:42.366 --> 06:44.333
Oh, boy.

06:47.033 --> 06:50.000
This is cool, right?
It leaks.

06:50.066 --> 06:53.033
But I got this thing.
It lands on this.

06:53.100 --> 06:55.766
What i-what is this
Who are you?

06:55.833 --> 06:59.333
Oliver. Uh, your new assistant.

06:59.400 --> 07:01.133
Torrie Bodnar,
that Kink editor.

07:01.200 --> 07:03.600
Said you could
use and abuse me.

07:03.666 --> 07:06.900
Oh, so, umm..

07:06.966 --> 07:09.766
You know anything
about photography?

07:09.833 --> 07:11.966
Just what you'll tell me.

07:12.033 --> 07:14.000
'But I can hang out
and do stuff.'

07:14.066 --> 07:16.533
I-I see. You're good
at stuff, huh?

07:18.133 --> 07:21.433
Well, listen, why don't you, uh,
stuff this behind the stike.

07:23.333 --> 07:25.266
Uh, stike?

07:25.333 --> 07:27.433
Yes, it's the big gray thing.

07:27.500 --> 07:29.466
Gray thing, cool.

07:29.533 --> 07:31.766
You know, you're red.

07:31.833 --> 07:34.300
- Very hot.
- What?

07:34.366 --> 07:36.700
Your aura, I can see it.

07:36.766 --> 07:39.500
It's about out to here.

07:39.566 --> 07:43.433
- It's red, very hot.
- It's hot.

07:43.500 --> 07:45.666
Yeah, you should
de-stress or something.

07:45.733 --> 07:48.933
Oh, I see, so I'm stressed
Is that what hot means?

07:49.000 --> 07:51.766
Either that, or you
used to be good and bad.

07:51.833 --> 07:53.100
'I'll read up on it.'

07:53.166 --> 07:54.833
I used to do crystals, but, uh

07:54.900 --> 07:56.533
auras are a real kick.

07:56.600 --> 07:58.366
Not totally on top them, yet.

07:58.433 --> 08:02.133
- Alert me when you are.
- 'Cool, you got it.'

08:02.200 --> 08:05.300
- Oh, how about I stuff this?
- 'Hey, stuff away.'

08:05.366 --> 08:07.666
Hey, you know what,
then grab that pile of props

08:07.733 --> 08:10.933
and drag 'em over in front
of the, uh, big gray thing.

08:11.000 --> 08:13.266
Yeah, the ones labeled "Ripper".

08:13.333 --> 08:14.700
Ha, like "Jack the Ripper"?

08:14.766 --> 08:16.133
One and the same.

08:16.200 --> 08:18.133
Whoa, hey, racky!

08:38.366 --> 08:40.300
'What do you see?'

08:43.000 --> 08:45.833
I see...Jody as the witch.

08:45.900 --> 08:47.933
Talk to me.
What do you think?

08:48.000 --> 08:50.733
Well, it's not exactly racky.

08:50.800 --> 08:52.300
Well, you've got
that stuff right.

08:52.366 --> 08:55.233
I'm looking at it too,
Oliver sneaked me a copy.

08:55.300 --> 08:56.366
Nice of him.

08:56.433 --> 08:57.566
Yeah, well, I've got
a job for you.

08:57.633 --> 09:00.566
A new one. One you&lt;i

09:00.633 --> 09:03.100
Oliver should have a setup
in your studio, right now.

09:03.166 --> 09:06.333
You should be doing
this one for the next 20 years.

09:14.966 --> 09:16.300
Congratulations!

09:16.366 --> 09:18.000
You're the new
official photographer

09:18.066 --> 09:21.600
for all the laminated
restaurant menus in the country.

09:21.666 --> 09:24.300
- You want it over here?
- What?

09:24.366 --> 09:26.400
You want it over here?

09:27.566 --> 09:29.933
'Uh, yeah, yeah, that's good.'

09:30.000 --> 09:32.666
I don't see what this
has to do with Halloween.

09:32.733 --> 09:34.966
I'm gonna pop right out of this.

09:35.033 --> 09:37.500
That's cool. Trick and treat.

09:37.566 --> 09:39.533
Oh, get back, buddy.

09:41.133 --> 09:43.633
So, I guess, uh,
a date is out of the question.

09:46.600 --> 09:48.200
Are we gonna do this?

09:48.266 --> 09:50.333
Yeah! Yeah, let's shoot it.

09:51.966 --> 09:54.233
'Umm, Oliver turn on
the fog machine'

09:54.300 --> 09:56.933
and, uh, then go down to
the camera store on the corner

09:57.000 --> 09:59.166
and ask 'em for Stoney's usual.

09:59.233 --> 10:01.766
I can do that.

10:01.833 --> 10:04.066
And have to be
real careful with this fog

10:04.133 --> 10:05.800
It's very slippery.

10:05.866 --> 10:08.166
I have a layout
in Paris next week.

10:08.233 --> 10:10.866
If I fall and break something,
we're talking big bucks here.

10:10.933 --> 10:14.000
Oh, so, don't fall.

10:14.066 --> 10:16.333
Well, we better it shoot
before my eyes get too red.

10:18.300 --> 10:20.600
Now, why are your
eyes gonna get red?

10:20.666 --> 10:23.033
Jordan Kingman's?

10:23.800 --> 10:25.433
Major had to be there.

10:25.500 --> 10:27.200
Always runs late.

10:27.266 --> 10:28.900
No sleep.

10:28.966 --> 10:30.966
Why don't you
just close your eyes?

10:31.033 --> 10:33.033
Rest against the lamp post?

10:34.366 --> 10:36.400
And don't say anything.

10:36.466 --> 10:38.833
'Just let the fog build up,
while I load the camera.'

11:02.666 --> 11:05.433
It's cold outside..

11:05.500 --> 11:07.733
...but death is colder.

11:09.033 --> 11:10.566
Not bad.

11:10.633 --> 11:12.700
But this is bad!

11:14.600 --> 11:17.033
No, uh-uh, no!

11:17.100 --> 11:18.366
That's wonderful! Wonderful!

11:18.433 --> 11:20.900
'Please! Please! Uh, aah!

11:27.366 --> 11:31.033
Ooh, my beautiful
show some emotion.

11:32.166 --> 11:33.900
'Please, please, no!'

11:36.800 --> 11:38.366
'Ah, no!'

11:38.433 --> 11:40.366
Oh, yes, my princess.

11:40.433 --> 11:41.733
Very good.

11:43.633 --> 11:46.200
Great! Super.
I love it, I love it!

11:46.266 --> 11:47.533
'Help me, God!'

11:49.566 --> 11:51.366
Just move, be loose, be loose.

11:51.433 --> 11:52.533
Keep yelling!

11:52.600 --> 11:54.500
And now, my beauty!

11:54.566 --> 11:57.533
Dance! Dance! Dance!

11:59.000 --> 12:01.066
Oh, my God!

12:03.533 --> 12:05.400
- Where'd he go?
- Are you okay?

12:05.466 --> 12:06.733
That was great!

12:06.800 --> 12:08.466
Come on, let's go again,
right away.

12:08.533 --> 12:10.133
Get away from me, you're crazy.

12:10.200 --> 12:12.400
- Why, what's wrong?
- Ask your sick-o friend.

12:15.633 --> 12:17.633
Oliver?

12:26.366 --> 12:28.533
You're out of there, pal.

12:28.600 --> 12:31.800
And tell Sally,
I'm keeping her leather jacket.

12:37.733 --> 12:40.333
Okay, I'm ready.
What do you want me to do?

12:40.400 --> 12:42.866
I'd like you to climb
in the coffin and get comfy.

12:47.966 --> 12:51.300
- Hello.
- Stoney Adler, Torrie Bodnar.

12:51.366 --> 12:52.433
Right both times.

12:52.500 --> 12:55.833
- 'It is the most..'
- Most what?

12:55.900 --> 12:58.433
"Jack The Ripper" stuff.
The most great photos!

12:58.500 --> 13:00.000
Dead on target!

13:00.066 --> 13:01.766
- You liked it?
- 'Yeah.'

13:01.833 --> 13:03.066
Great! Take it even further!

13:03.133 --> 13:05.066
Right to the edge.
Make it controversial.

13:05.133 --> 13:07.366
Maybe even insulting.
We'll sell more magazines.

13:07.433 --> 13:09.933
- Yeah, hey, I'll crank it up!
- 'Yeah.'

13:10.000 --> 13:11.633
Pour on the heat.

13:11.700 --> 13:13.266
I am red and hot.

13:13.333 --> 13:15.600
I knew we had the same aura.

13:15.666 --> 13:18.733
- I'm sorry to hear that.
- 'What?'

13:18.800 --> 13:21.533
I said how about that?

13:21.600 --> 13:23.066
Listen, I gotta go.

13:23.133 --> 13:25.933
Yeah, go, go, go, go!

13:32.666 --> 13:35.366
Okay, let's rock 'n' roll,
shall we?

13:35.433 --> 13:38.000
You know, these teeth
don't fit so well.

13:38.066 --> 13:41.300
- Oh, leave it.
- Yeah, we'll make it work.

13:41.366 --> 13:43.633
Yeah, a little jet-lagged
from my gig in the&lt;i

13:43.700 --> 13:45.433
so if I nod off, just nudge me.

13:45.500 --> 13:46.566
Okay.

13:46.633 --> 13:49.733
Umm, Kiki, I want you
to grab this wooden stake

13:49.800 --> 13:51.600
and hold it above you.

13:51.666 --> 13:54.066
And I want you to hold it as
though someone is trying to

13:54.133 --> 13:55.633
drive it in, you know.

13:55.700 --> 13:58.166
And I want you to fight with it.

13:58.233 --> 14:01.066
Okay, you want
erotic, weird, sick

14:01.133 --> 14:02.800
funny, goofy, I'm up for it.

14:02.866 --> 14:05.800
Uh, how about, uh, racky?

14:07.900 --> 14:09.833
Yeah, cool.

14:09.900 --> 14:11.400
'Hey, I can see that.'

14:11.466 --> 14:13.000
So, you want me to
lick the stick?

14:13.066 --> 14:14.900
Or I could suck
on it if you want.

14:14.966 --> 14:16.566
'Uh, no, no, no, no.'

14:16.633 --> 14:18.800
I think just fight
with it for now.

14:18.866 --> 14:21.300
Maybe we'll, uh, lick later.

14:21.366 --> 14:23.000
Oh! Oh, no.

14:23.066 --> 14:26.366
Oliver, uh, would go out

14:26.433 --> 14:28.733
and get some fog juice please?

14:28.800 --> 14:31.133
You got it.

14:31.200 --> 14:34.600
Hey, you just relax and, uh,
I'm gonna change some lenses.

14:57.100 --> 14:58.533
Hey, babe!

14:58.600 --> 15:00.866
Stakes get to impale hearts.

15:00.933 --> 15:02.933
Get him off of me!

15:03.000 --> 15:04.133
Oh, Ki..

15:04.200 --> 15:05.500
Hey, that's great!

15:05.566 --> 15:07.166
Keep doing that, really..

15:07.233 --> 15:08.900
Get him off me!

15:08.966 --> 15:10.400
Get him off..

15:13.900 --> 15:16.800
I heard you was
dying for this job.

15:25.766 --> 15:27.000
Nice touch, Kiki, that's it.

15:27.066 --> 15:29.000
Shudder like you're dying
and you're fighting it.

15:33.666 --> 15:34.766
That nails it.

15:34.833 --> 15:37.133
You just relax,
I'm gonna knock these off.

15:54.700 --> 15:56.866
- Ready?
- Oh, yeah.

15:56.933 --> 15:58.100
Super rush.

15:58.166 --> 16:00.700
Get these prints
off to Torrie's, right away.

16:00.766 --> 16:02.900
Flying out.

16:09.233 --> 16:11.366
Well, we're about through here.

16:11.433 --> 16:12.700
This is your nudge.

16:12.766 --> 16:16.166
Here, I'll take this.
You can let go.

16:16.233 --> 16:18.200
Oh, my God!

16:20.733 --> 16:22.666
Oh, my God!

16:22.733 --> 16:25.333
This can't be.

16:25.400 --> 16:27.733
Well, she's dead.

16:27.800 --> 16:30.100
Oh, Oliver!

16:31.300 --> 16:33.466
Oh!

16:33.533 --> 16:34.700
Wait a minute.

16:34.766 --> 16:36.066
This can't be.

16:36.133 --> 16:39.800
Uh, alright,
pull yourself together.

16:39.866 --> 16:43.700
Uh, police.

16:43.766 --> 16:46.666
Urgh, I-I can't call the police.

16:46.733 --> 16:50.200
They're gonna think I did it.
I-I'm alone here.

16:50.266 --> 16:53.133
Okay, wait a minute,
wait a minute.

16:53.200 --> 16:55.900
My prints are on the stake.

16:55.966 --> 16:57.166
And I s..

16:57.233 --> 17:00.300
Stake is in the photos,
I sent the photos out.

17:00.366 --> 17:02.433
Okay!

17:02.500 --> 17:04.400
Wait, I just need time.

17:04.466 --> 17:06.433
I need time to think.

17:06.500 --> 17:09.633
I know what I'll do.

17:09.700 --> 17:12.166
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

17:12.233 --> 17:13.800
I'll stash the body.

17:35.566 --> 17:38.933
There must be something.

17:39.000 --> 17:40.933
Something, I missed.

18:00.366 --> 18:02.200
Who the hell are you?

18:02.266 --> 18:04.600
'Your meal ticket.'

18:07.333 --> 18:08.366
Where are you?

18:08.433 --> 18:10.100
'In your head, dummy.'

18:10.166 --> 18:12.100
No!

18:13.000 --> 18:15.233
In-in my dream?

18:15.300 --> 18:17.133
'We've been working together.'

18:17.200 --> 18:20.200
